OL,3,CC4 marketing of controversial
OL,4,Cprogramme purely about chasing ratings?
OL,6,FOthers would argue it is actually an
OL,7,Fattempt to challenge those views and
OL,8,Fengage people who might not watch a
OL,9,Fconventional documentary.
OL,11,FThere are sincerely held views on both
OL,12,Fsides of this argument.
OL,14,FIn some respects, this programme is a
OL,15,Freminder of the glory days of Channel
OL,16,F4 ` days when the channel would often
OL,17,Fshow provocative and controversial
OL,18,Fcontent.
OL,20,FInevitably lines were sometimes
OL,21,Fcrossed but you don't always know
OL,22,Fwhere a line is until it is crossed.
