OL,3,CC4 marketing of controversial
OL,4,Cprogramme purely about chasing ratings?
OL,6,FBut in the glory days of Channel 4,
OL,7,Fthere were two important checks and
OL,8,Fbalances to edgy content.
OL,10,FFirst of all, Channel 4's announcers
OL,11,Fdid a great job guiding viewers
OL,12,Fthrough a diverse schedule.
OL,14,FThoughtful intros to programmes helped
OL,15,Fset the scene and played a part in
OL,16,Fensuring viewers understood what a
OL,17,Fprogramme was trying to achieve.
