OL,3,CC4 marketing of controversial
OL,4,Cprogramme purely about chasing ratings?
OL,6,FWhen complaints came in, they were
OL,7,Fsometimes from people who had switched
OL,8,Fon half way through or who had no
OL,9,Finterest in what the programme
OL,10,Factually set out to do.
OL,12,FHowever on Monday, the announcer's
OL,13,Fintro to Go Back to Where You Came
OL,14,FFrom correctly flagged up all the
OL,15,Fcompliance issues with the programme
OL,16,F(strong language, offensive views etc)
OL,17,Fbut did little to set the context for
OL,18,Fit.
OL,20,FProvocative on air promotions ` which
OL,21,Fincluded offensive views ` did not
OL,22,Fhelp either.
