OL,3,CC4 marketing of controversial
OL,4,Cprogramme purely about chasing ratings?
OL,6,FOf course, the aspirations of a
OL,7,Fprogramme are one thing ` whether it
OL,8,Fsucceeds is another.
OL,10,FWith any provocative output, viewers'
OL,11,Fopinions will inevitably be split.
OL,13,FC4 historically showed great respect
OL,14,Ffor its viewers. Their views were
OL,15,Frepresented on air and they were
OL,16,Fallowed to talk to programme makers as
OL,17,Fequals.
