OL,3,CC4 marketing of controversial
OL,4,Cprogramme purely about chasing ratings?
OL,6,FThis is why some once held C4 in such
OL,7,Fhigh regard. It was possible to
OL,8,Frespect a channel which commissioned a
OL,9,Fprogramme you took exception to if
OL,10,Fthat channel also accepted that the
OL,11,Fviews of critics were just as valid as
OL,12,Fthe opinions of supporters.
OL,14,FWith no forum for debate nowadays, it
OL,15,Fis easy to assume the worth of a
OL,16,Fprogramme is only about its ratings or
OL,17,Fthe ad revenue brought in.
OL,19,FTime for C4 to think about just what
OL,20,Fits announcers should be saying and to
OL,21,Freflect on its corporate marketing.
